FBIS3-4515 "drchi062_a_94008" FBIS-CHI-94-062 Document Type:Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Briefing French Prime Minister To Visit 7-10 Apr OW3103092394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0911 GMT 31 Mar 94 OW3103092394 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, March 31 (XINHUA) -- French Prime Minister Edouard Balladur will pay an official visit to China from April 7 to 10 as guest of Premier Li Peng, announced a Foreign Ministry spokesman here today. Speaking at weekly press conference, the spokesman said that Balladur's China tour is "an important political visit." "It will give major impetus to the further development of the bilateral ties between China and France, including economic and trade relations," he said. Maintaining good political relations will provide a solid foundation and favorable conditions for the development of mutually beneficial economic and trade relations between the two countries, he said.
